Before ORM, developers wrote 
.........................


plain JDBC code. You'd manually create a connection, write SQL strings,
execute them, loop through ResultSets, and map each column to a Java field by hand. It worked - but it was
tedious, error-prone, and full of boilerplate.
Here's a rough idea of what that looked like:
// Without ORM - old school JDBC
