Transaction Management	
========================

=> Tx means single unit amount of work.

=> When we perform DML (insert, update, delete) operations with database then tx are very very important.

Note: For select operations tx is not required.	

				sender account -----------------> reciever account

				-- deduct amt here ----------------- credit amount here

				    -- op-1 success	-----------------   op-2 failed

=> If both operations are successfull then we will call it as sucessfull transaction.

Note: If tx is successful then we should commit that tx. Commit means saving data changes permanently in database.

=> If any one operation is failed then we will call it as failure transaction.

Note: If tx is failed then we should rollback that tx. Rollback means undo our dml operation.

Note: When we are working with Transactions we need to follow Atomocity principle.

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~ Atomicity Means either all or none. ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

@Transactional
